race.comment: DASHING DONKEY (1) was second to AZEOLA (scratched) last time when beaten under a length. He struggles to win but has claims off his last start performance in what looks a wide open race. PARABELLUM (7) is going okay, not far away of late, beaten 3.5 lengths at Albury in a Bm58 last start. Should prove hard to hold out if Duffy can get on the back of the right horse from a tricky gate. WHISTLER GIRL (6) wasn't beaten far at St Arnaud last time out and had been good in two runs prior, winning three back at Gunbower. She can roll forward here and take catching. TALLINGAS PRINCE (5) will find this a bit easier than his past couple and could be an improver.
